ANSWERS TO ASSIGNMENT README QUESTIONS (if applicable):
1. The probability of two heads, one head and one tail and two tails is 25%, 50%,25% respectively.
   Because we have two coins, we can name them coin1 and coin2. Consider one head and one tail, 
   coin1 could be head and coin2 could be tail,on contrary, coin1 could be tail and coin2 could be 
   head.So the probability of one head and one tail could be two times of the other two.

2. By 5000 trials, 2%
   By 10000 trials, 0-1%
   So, about 500~10000 trials, I can get results within 1% of these probabilities.

3. My program can do Integer.MAX(which means the maxim of int type in java) trials.
   If we input a number bigger than Integer.MAX, it will overflow.
   



